{
  "metadata": {
    "intent": "Closed-trophic-web probe (extends example12, issue #136). Take example12_generalist_dominance's proven-viable, differentiated world UNCHANGED and add the one role the legacy suite has never combined with a live green web -- a guild of 8 sessile FACULTATIVE detritivores (photosynthetic_absorption 0.25 + heterotrophy 0.6, mobility 0; heterotroph-dominant so the sim classifies them as decomposers, but with just enough autotrophy to clear baseline metabolism between carcass meals) -- placed ON the producer ring (r=31, one unit inside the r=32 producers) so they sit WITHIN the 2.5-unit feeding reach of the ring's carcass rain. This is the deliberate inversion of example9, where the decomposer was held OUT of reach to force a pure-detrital diet on a hand-placed deposit; here the decomposers live among the dying, so the brown loop (producer/consumer -> carcass -> decomposer -> nutrient return) closes INSIDE a living, self-thinning economy. A small starter carcass (600 energy) is co-located with each decomposer purely to bridge establishment (drawn down within the first ~150 of 2000 ticks) -- the deliberate contrast with example9's 12000-energy deposit sized to outlast the run, so a guild alive at tick 2000 is sustained by the living carcass rain plus its modest autotrophy, not the starter. KEY DESIGN LESSON established empirically while authoring this file: an OBLIGATE saprotroph guild (photosynthetic_absorption 0) STARVES OUT by ~tick 40 even when placed in-reach -- the living carcass rain alone cannot sustain a decomposer (confirming example9's deposit-dependence) -- and a too-autotrophic / too-numerous guild (e.g. 16 x photo 0.3) inverts the pyramid (decomposers out-compete producers, trophic_balance -> 0). A LEAN, heterotroph-dominant facultative guild is the narrow honest band that both persists AND preserves a producer-led pyramid.",
    "source_issue": 136,
    "roster": "Inherits example12 verbatim -- 24 specialist producers (autotrophy 0.45, sessile, ring r=32); 8 specialist mobile consumers; 10 broad generalists; 10 compatible sessile mixotrophs -- PLUS 8 sessile facultative detritivores (photosynthetic_absorption 0.25, heterotrophy 0.6, mobility 0, kappa 0.45, fecundity 0.25, reserve 120) evenly spaced on the ring at r=31 (every 45deg), each on a 600-energy starter carcass within 2.5 units of the ring's carcass fall. 60 living agents + 8 seeded carcasses.",
    "probes": "nutrient_lockup",
    "prediction": "live",
    "rationale": "A-priori viability CANNOT decide decomposer viability: it is turnover- and reach-dependent, a dynamics property the lens explicitly classifies as having no clean existence gate ('nutrient lockup has no clean existence gate', viability.md) because both sides of the decomposer-return floor -- achievable carcass richness and decomposer reach -- are endogenous. So this scenario is handed to observation. The closed-form characterisation the lens CAN state is the falsifiable prediction C* = death_flux / decomp_turnover: unlike example9, where the producer ring's carcass rain fell OUTSIDE any decomposer's reach (decomp_turnover -> 0, C* -> full death flux, observed nutrient_lockup 8/8), here decomp_turnover is bounded above zero by construction (decomposers sit in the carcass-fall band), so C* should sit below the full death flux and the available pool stays above the reproduction floor. OBSERVED (8-seed ensemble; observed.json / verdicts.md): prediction confirmed -- failure=none 8/8, fitness ~0.69 (at or above example12's 0.67), clustering 1.0 AND trophic_balance 1.0 (a producer-led pyramid, ~9-11 producers > 8 decomposers, NOT inverted). The decomposer guild PERSISTS as a reproducing lineage (8-9 of 8 alive at tick 2000 on every seed -- the first persisting decomposer lineage inside a live differentiated web in the suite, where example9 sustained a single non-reproducing deposit-fed individual). The brown loop demonstrably CARRIES FLUX: carcass-locked nutrient is cut ~40% vs the no-decomposer example12 baseline (median ~2300 vs ~3900). HONEST CAVEAT -- closure is PARTIAL, not complete: the dead pool is reduced, not eliminated (carcass COUNT actually rises, ~610 vs baseline ~410, because the sustained guild adds standing biomass that later dies). 8 sessile decomposers with a structure-independent 2.5-unit reach (body_reach_coefficient = 0) cannot blanket the ~190-unit ring circumference, so much carcass-fall is never reached. Full field-scale closure is reach-limited -- exactly the endogenous 'decomposer reach' term viability.md names as the under-committed knob whose commitment (body_reach_coefficient > 0, or a mobile detritivore the autotrophy-mobility incompatibility currently kills) would be required to close the brown loop completely. So: structural + partial-functional closure of the brown loop inside a living web, with the residual gap localised to a single missing mechanism the viability lens already names.",
    "geometry": "Decomposers at r=31 at the 8 producer angles {0,45,...,315}deg, each ~1 unit radially inside a producer (r=32) and within 2.5 units of consumer/mixotroph deaths (r=28-30). Starter carcasses co-located at the decomposer positions.",
    "status": "current -- every WorldParameter specified explicitly (inherits example12's fully-specified block verbatim); decomposer trait vector is a lean heterotroph-dominant facultative detritivore (the obligate and the over-autotrophic/over-numerous variants were tested and rejected, see intent). Ensemble outcome computed via eval_scenarios; entry added to observed.json and judged in verdicts.md."
  },
